<paragraph blockId="2.[151,560,1550,1610]" box="[151,266,1585,1610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,258,1585,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,339,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1625]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Cercyothrips: (1) pronotum, mesonotum and metanotum; (2) sternites IV – VI. Scirtidothrips: (3) pronotum, mesonotum and metanotum; (4) tergites III – V. Ephedrothrips ontigolae (paratype): (5) pronotum; (6) tergites III – V. Scirtothrips palloris (Hood) comb. n: (7) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239147/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Figs 
<number box="[215,258,1585,1610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1657,1862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Two species are placed in this genus, from 
<collectingCountry box="[665,766,1658,1681]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Morocco</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[828,895,1657,1682]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Spain</collectingCountry>
. These were described as having 
<number box="[1293,1306,1657,1682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented maxillary palps, a character state shared only with 
<taxonomicName box="[736,881,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Cercyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[736,881,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Cercyothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the genera discussed here. However, the presence or absence of a distal suture on these palps is sometimes difficult to determine, and one 
<typeStatus box="[1274,1370,1730,1754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Ephedrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ontigolae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">E. ontigolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<collectionCode box="[306,389,1766,1790]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/jgkc-cvji" name="Faculdad de Biologia, Departamento de Zoologia" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">UCME</collectionCode>
) has been studied that appears to have two segments on the right palp but three on the left palp. The form of the setae on the pterothorax (
<figureCitation box="[703,772,1801,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,339,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1625]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Cercyothrips: (1) pronotum, mesonotum and metanotum; (2) sternites IV – VI. Scirtidothrips: (3) pronotum, mesonotum and metanotum; (4) tergites III – V. Ephedrothrips ontigolae (paratype): (5) pronotum; (6) tergites III – V. Scirtothrips palloris (Hood) comb. n: (7) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239147/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Fig. 
<number box="[758,772,1801,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) and fore wings is different from that found in any other genus in the 
<taxonomicName box="[293,425,1837,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,425,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Scirtothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
